definition: to fill or stuff/(of a form etc) to fill in
exterior surface/family relationship via females/to show (one's opinion)/a model/a table (listing information)/a form/a meter (measuring sth)

sentences.english: Form-filling guides and the required courses for specialization could be found in the application form.
sentences.chinese: 填表說明及專業方向對應課程詳見申請表。

sentences.english: Please read the Notes for Application overleaf before completing this form.
sentences.chinese: 填表前請參考背頁之申請注意事項。

sentences.english: I explained the importance of being truthful on the application, and he began filling out his paper work.
sentences.chinese: 我解釋了填申請時誠實的重要性，他就開始填表格。

sentences.english: You should complete a separate application form for scheduled service(s).
sentences.chinese: 申請專線服務，必須另填表格。

sentences.english: All day long, he mindlessly filled out forms.
sentences.chinese: 他一整天都在機械麻木地填表格。

sentences.english: Athlete who lost the card shall replace a new card with HK$30.00 and complete this form again.
sentences.chinese: 補領的運動員須重新填表，費用爲港幣三十元正。

sentences.english: Exchange information and fill in the chart.
I will fill out the form for you. What is your name?
sentences.chinese: 我幫你填表格，你叫什麼名字？

sentences.english: He filled in the form in ink.
Then write clearly the reasons and fill in all the columns by referring to the instruction.
sentences.chinese: 把退稅理由寫清楚，填寫各欄時請參閱填表說明。

sentences.english: Please read carefully the important notes on the last page before filling out the form.
sentences.chinese: 請申請人認真閱讀本表第四頁的填表說明。

sentences.english: On-line pre-registration and badge printing saves you from form filling and queuing on-site.
sentences.chinese: 網上預登記自助打印胸卡，無需現場填表排隊。

sentences.english: Please read the accompanying information pamphlet before completing this form.
sentences.chinese: 填表前請參閱隨附的資料簡章。

sentences.english: It saves you the burden of completing web forms over the internet with intelligent form filler.
sentences.chinese: 這樣可以節省你完成了用智能填表互聯網形式的負擔。

sentences.english: Again, remember to bring a pen, pass completing the convenient.
sentences.chinese: 再記得帶筆，過關填表方便。

definition: to fill in a form/to write data in a box (on a questionnaire or web form)
receipt (written acknowledgement of receipt of an item)
to fill in a form for sb else
to sign up/to enter one's name/to apply/to register/to enroll/to enlist
to act for sb else/to act on sb's behalf/an agent/a diplomatic representative/a chargé d'affaires
abbr. for 體格檢查|体格检查[ti3 ge2 jian3 cha2]
